1
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:18,833
[bell tolls]

2
00:00:18,917 --> 00:00:22,292
- [tense music playing]
- I swear before the Emerald Buddha…

3
00:00:22,375 --> 00:00:24,750
…the City Pillar Guardian Spirit,
Phra Siam Devadhiraj…

4
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:27,500
…and all sacred beings…

5
00:00:27,583 --> 00:00:30,500
…that I will testify before this court
and speak the whole truth.

6
00:00:30,583 --> 00:00:34,042
[Somchai] If I should speak a single word
of falsehood,

7
00:00:34,125 --> 00:00:37,458
may all danger and disaster

8
00:00:37,542 --> 00:00:40,125
befall me at once.

9
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:44,250
[music concludes]

10
00:00:44,833 --> 00:00:46,542
Could you please tell us

11
00:00:46,625 --> 00:00:49,042
what you were doing
on the night of the incident?

12
00:00:49,708 --> 00:00:50,750
[Somchai] Hmm…

13
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,583
I remember that day was a Friday.

14
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:55,500
It was around six in the evening.

15
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:58,417
I was at Mr. Sorn's house.

16
00:00:59,625 --> 00:01:03,917
We were sitting under
Mr. Sorn's stilt house.

17
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,042
[whimsical music playing]

18
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:10,042
[Somchai]<i> I saw Mr. Mai come back</i>
<i>on his motorcycle.</i>

19
00:01:10,125 --> 00:01:11,583
- [Jittri] <i>One moment.</i>
- [music stops]

20
00:01:11,667 --> 00:01:13,333
[Mai imitates bird call]

21
00:01:14,583 --> 00:01:16,458
- [Somchai] Hmm?
- Were you there alone?

22
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:21,875
No, not at all. There were three of us.

23
00:01:21,958 --> 00:01:26,625
<i>Mr. Sirikorn and Mr. Tawanchai,</i>
<i>the school principal, were also there.</i>

24
00:01:26,708 --> 00:01:29,917
- [perky music playing]
- Hey! Come on, over here!

25
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,042
Mai! Oh, wow!

26
00:01:32,125 --> 00:01:36,250
Long time no see. You've grown up
to be handsome, just like me. [laughs]

27
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,250
Hey, about that forestry position…

28
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:40,625
- I'll take care of it for you.
- Thank you, sir.

29
00:01:40,708 --> 00:01:42,542
- [Somchai] Alright, cheers!
- [glasses clink]

30
00:01:42,625 --> 00:01:43,833
[all laughing]

31
00:01:43,917 --> 00:01:47,042
[Somchai] <i>We sat there from evening</i>
<i>until late at night.</i>

32
00:01:47,125 --> 00:01:48,708
<i>Just a casual get-together.</i>

33
00:01:48,792 --> 00:01:50,458
- [overlapping chatter]
- [pop music playing]

34
00:01:50,542 --> 00:01:51,792
Here's more food!

35
00:01:52,292 --> 00:01:53,375
The mayor drinks first!

36
00:01:53,458 --> 00:01:55,750
[group chattering, laughing]

37
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:58,792
[Somchai]<i> And after that,</i>
<i>we all went home.</i>

38
00:01:58,875 --> 00:02:00,208
[music stops abruptly]

39
00:02:00,292 --> 00:02:01,333
[Sorn] Hey.

40
00:02:02,417 --> 00:02:03,833
What?!

41
00:02:03,917 --> 00:02:05,667
[quirky music playing]

42
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:07,833
By the time I drove home,

43
00:02:07,917 --> 00:02:11,208
- it was around, hmm…
- [Jittri clears throat gently]

44
00:02:11,292 --> 00:02:12,708
[music stops abruptly]

45
00:02:12,792 --> 00:02:13,875
[Somchai] Hmm?

46
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,792
[clears throat gently]

47
00:02:15,875 --> 00:02:18,083
Uh… [hesitates]

48
00:02:18,167 --> 00:02:19,708
Oh, no, not yet.

49
00:02:19,792 --> 00:02:21,583
We hadn't even started the karaoke yet.

50
00:02:21,667 --> 00:02:24,417
<i>♪ You wouldn't believe me</i>
<i>If I swore on it ♪</i>

51
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:27,542
- [upbeat rock song playing]
<i>- ♪ A tiger's heart behind that face ♪</i>

52
00:02:27,625 --> 00:02:30,500
<i>♪ I didn't listen to the warnings ♪</i>

53
00:02:30,583 --> 00:02:32,708
<i>♪ And gave you my heart… ♪</i>

54
00:02:32,792 --> 00:02:34,750
[Sirikorn]
<i>I intended to sing just one song.</i>

55
00:02:34,833 --> 00:02:36,500
<i>But once I had the mic, I couldn't stop.</i>

56
00:02:36,583 --> 00:02:40,250
<i>Next thing I knew, it was past midnight.</i>
<i>That's when my wife called.</i>

57
00:02:40,333 --> 00:02:42,375
Yeah, I'm heading home now.

58
00:02:42,875 --> 00:02:44,125
[woman] <i>Are you drunk?</i>

59
00:02:44,625 --> 00:02:47,917
Who's drunk? Not me.
We're just drinking water.

60
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:50,250
<i>♪ Don't believe it, don't believe it ♪</i>

61
00:02:52,167 --> 00:02:55,917
[group] We're heading out. Bye-bye!

62
00:02:57,458 --> 00:02:59,250
[song concludes]

63
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:01,458
[slurring] I'm not drunk! I'm not leaving!

64
00:03:01,542 --> 00:03:04,875
[Sirikorn] <i>But we can confirm</i>
<i>that Mr. Mai was with us all night.</i>

65
00:03:04,958 --> 00:03:07,042
There's no way he could have shot anyone.

66
00:03:07,667 --> 00:03:08,667
[Jeng] That's a lie!

67
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:11,417
I saw that bastard Mai shoot him!
You're all in on it, damn it!

68
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,042
[crowd clamoring]

69
00:03:13,125 --> 00:03:15,208
[Jeng] You're all bastards!

70
00:03:15,708 --> 00:03:18,500
What the hell are you smiling at?!

71
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,333
[judge 1] Everyone, stop!

72
00:03:21,125 --> 00:03:22,875
Stop! Stop it, right now!

73
00:03:22,958 --> 00:03:24,625
[Jittri] I ask the court to consider this.

74
00:03:24,708 --> 00:03:27,333
On one hand, we have upstanding
government officials.

75
00:03:27,417 --> 00:03:29,542
And on the other, a monk
who lets people drink alcohol

76
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:31,542
and turn a temple into a nightclub.

77
00:03:31,625 --> 00:03:33,708
Who is more credible?

78
00:03:33,792 --> 00:03:35,167
[dramatic music plays]

79
00:03:35,250 --> 00:03:36,833
[music fades]

80
00:03:36,917 --> 00:03:39,542
<i>♪ You wouldn't believe me</i>
<i>If I swore on it ♪</i>

81
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:42,875
- [upbeat rock song playing]
<i>- ♪ A tiger's heart behind that face ♪</i>

82
00:03:42,958 --> 00:03:45,458
<i>♪ I didn't listen to the warnings ♪</i>

83
00:03:45,542 --> 00:03:48,708
<i>♪ And gave you my heart ♪</i>

84
00:03:48,792 --> 00:03:51,292
<i>♪ You wouldn't believe me</i>
<i>If I swore on it ♪</i>

85
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:54,375
<i>♪ That innocent face can't be trusted ♪</i>

86
00:03:54,458 --> 00:03:57,500
<i>♪ You've broken so many hearts ♪</i>

87
00:03:57,583 --> 00:04:00,042
<i>♪ How many have there been? ♪</i>

88
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:01,583
<i>♪ Have you ever even counted? ♪</i>

89
00:04:03,458 --> 00:04:05,750
[song concludes]

90
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:11,667
THE EVIL LAWYER

91
00:04:12,792 --> 00:04:14,625
[birds singing]

92
00:04:14,708 --> 00:04:17,875
[woman] I'm aware that
the current fishery laws

93
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:20,250
have created significant problems
for the business sector.

94
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:23,625
Employers are afraid to hire anyone
for fear of breaking the law.

95
00:04:23,708 --> 00:04:25,375
SECRETARY-GENERAL
LABOR ALLIES FOUNDATION

96
00:04:25,458 --> 00:04:27,958
But this new law, which you claim
will solve the labor shortage,

97
00:04:28,042 --> 00:04:30,875
is lenient on both penalties
and preventative measures.

98
00:04:31,708 --> 00:04:33,833
If I were being a bit cynical,

99
00:04:33,917 --> 00:04:37,542
I'd think you were trying to facilitate
human trafficking.

100
00:04:38,625 --> 00:04:40,792
[moderator]
Please be careful with your words.

101
00:04:40,875 --> 00:04:42,833
There's no need for such accusations.

102
00:04:43,708 --> 00:04:44,750
Let's discuss this calmly.

103
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:46,917
I've been proposing this for a long time.

104
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,500
If you're going to reject
my proposal again,

105
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:51,667
let me be clear.

106
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:55,750
Anyone involved with this bill

107
00:04:55,833 --> 00:04:58,208
is a supporter of human trafficking.

108
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:04,333
I think we should all calm down.

109
00:05:04,417 --> 00:05:07,833
The fishing industry is facing
a severe crisis right now.

110
00:05:07,917 --> 00:05:10,875
I propose we pass this bill for now.

111
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:14,958
If anyone still has concerns
about labor welfare,

112
00:05:15,042 --> 00:05:16,708
we can address it in a subordinate law

113
00:05:16,792 --> 00:05:19,125
and consider it separately later.
How's that?

114
00:05:19,208 --> 00:05:22,208
The subordinate law I proposed
which you already rejected?

115
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:27,042
Dr. Atchara, you were one of the people
who voted against my proposal.

116
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:29,208
[soft tense music playing]

117
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,792
And now you're bringing this up again.

118
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:37,250
How can I be sure
that you'll keep your word?

119
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:40,750
[Ang] Excuse me.

120
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:47,750
My name is Angsumalin Thumnart,
an advisor for the Ruam Thai Party.

121
00:05:48,667 --> 00:05:51,250
I'd like to take two minutes of your time.

122
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,917
I'd like to inform Ms. Pawaree

123
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,583
that our party has drafted
another subordinate bill,

124
00:05:56,667 --> 00:05:59,083
specifically to protect maritime workers.

125
00:05:59,167 --> 00:06:01,417
And we're about to introduce it
to parliament.

126
00:06:02,167 --> 00:06:05,042
I wasn't aware of the proposal
you presented.

127
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,000
But I hope we can discuss it later.

128
00:06:08,792 --> 00:06:12,292
Perhaps you could offer some advice
on things we might have missed.

129
00:06:12,375 --> 00:06:14,667
I've been a human rights lawyer
for many years.

130
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,917
Rest assured, I understand
the importance of this issue.

131
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:26,292
[music concludes]

132
00:06:26,958 --> 00:06:28,375
[Ang] Ms. Pawaree?

133
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,292
I'm Angsumalin.

134
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:33,792
An advisor to the leader
of the Ruam Thai Party.

135
00:06:36,333 --> 00:06:38,375
You can call me Pang. What is it?

136
00:06:38,458 --> 00:06:39,917
Please don't worry.

137
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,083
I've already proposed that the party
submit the fishery law amendment.

138
00:06:43,167 --> 00:06:44,542
I don't know how far it'll get.

139
00:06:44,625 --> 00:06:47,042
But I can promise you
I'll do my absolute best.

140
00:06:47,792 --> 00:06:49,375
You're going to face a lot of obstacles.

141
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:50,917
I'm not getting my hopes up.

142
00:06:51,583 --> 00:06:55,042
But it's good to see someone
who's genuinely trying to help.

143
00:06:56,625 --> 00:06:59,833
These days, the migrant workers
are in serious trouble.

144
00:06:59,917 --> 00:07:01,708
The fishing industry is the worst of all.

145
00:07:01,792 --> 00:07:07,083
They're injured, killed, disabled.
And countless have gone missing.

146
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:08,958
I see cases like this every day.

147
00:07:09,042 --> 00:07:11,167
Where do you find these cases?

148
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:14,125
They're sent to us by our network.

149
00:07:14,208 --> 00:07:17,292
But we also have workers
who contact the center directly.

150
00:07:17,375 --> 00:07:18,458
Quite often too.

151
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:21,792
Could I ask you for a favor?

152
00:07:25,583 --> 00:07:28,458
I need your help finding
a woman from Myanmar.

153
00:07:29,458 --> 00:07:31,917
[foreboding music playing]

154
00:07:51,542 --> 00:07:53,875
- [player] Let me take a look.
- [Suwat laughs]

155
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:57,833
[indistinct chatter]

156
00:07:57,917 --> 00:07:59,250
Ah! [chuckles]

157
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,875
Let me see. Wow.

158
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:08,542
[Suwat] Okay. Let's see.

159
00:08:08,625 --> 00:08:09,542
Hmm?

160
00:08:10,042 --> 00:08:11,125
[laughs]

161
00:08:11,708 --> 00:08:13,500
[in English] Mr. Suwat, hello.

162
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:14,875
[Suwat] Hello.

163
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:18,000
Imperial Pu'er tea, a gift from Mr. Zhou.

164
00:08:18,083 --> 00:08:19,167
Thank you.

165
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:20,458
[in Thai] Wow.

166
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:22,167
[in English] Hi, Andy. Have a seat.

167
00:08:22,250 --> 00:08:23,958
[in Thai] This must be my lucky day.

168
00:08:24,042 --> 00:08:26,292
Him showing up is a good omen.

169
00:08:26,375 --> 00:08:27,542
[chuckles]

170
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:29,042
[Suwat] Brought me a gift too.

171
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:31,750
[in English] It's from Honduras.
This is my personal collection.

172
00:08:31,833 --> 00:08:33,792
- Please.
- Thank you.

173
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:35,917
[inhales deeply]

174
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:39,750
[Andy] The boss sends his thanks.

175
00:08:40,292 --> 00:08:41,875
Please don't overwork yourself.

176
00:08:43,917 --> 00:08:48,792
I'm just doing my job as any
old policeman could do.

177
00:08:48,875 --> 00:08:50,125
[music concludes]

178
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:55,167
An old policeman who can convince my boss
to buy a whole fishing fleet,

179
00:08:56,083 --> 00:08:58,833
knowing very well
that the regulations are strict.

180
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:02,208
- You must be very confident.
- [chuckles softly]

181
00:09:03,375 --> 00:09:04,375
[Suwat] Mm-hmm…

182
00:09:06,042 --> 00:09:07,792
Tell your boss,

183
00:09:07,875 --> 00:09:09,917
it's going to be worth it.

184
00:09:10,917 --> 00:09:13,333
As soon as Mr. Suwat

185
00:09:13,417 --> 00:09:17,375
and the Ruam Thai Party
pass the new law this term.

186
00:09:17,458 --> 00:09:19,083
[dealer speaking indistinctly]

187
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:21,375
[suspenseful music playing]

188
00:09:22,583 --> 00:09:23,875
[Suwat] Hmm.

189
00:09:27,417 --> 00:09:29,250
- [Anan] Ah.
- [dealer] Your move, sir.

190
00:09:29,917 --> 00:09:31,708
- [Anan] I call.
- [player] Hmm.

191
00:09:31,792 --> 00:09:32,958
I fold.

192
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,708
[Suwat] Buddy, what's your move?

193
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:43,500
[Andy in English] I'm all in.

194
00:09:49,417 --> 00:09:51,333
[Suwat laughing]

195
00:09:52,042 --> 00:09:54,292
[in Thai] This kid's got some nerve.

196
00:09:54,375 --> 00:09:56,000
[men laughing]

197
00:09:57,667 --> 00:09:59,542
I'm never one to back down.

198
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,667
Luck is on my side.

199
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:05,333
[dealer] Mr. Andy's got two pair.

200
00:10:05,417 --> 00:10:07,083
[Suwat laughing]

201
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:09,875
Going all-in with a hand like that?

202
00:10:10,542 --> 00:10:11,667
Wow.

203
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:14,167
Acting so tough with a hand like that.

204
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:16,208
[dealer] Mr. Suwat won with a full house.

205
00:10:16,292 --> 00:10:19,583
If you'll excuse me, I'll help myself.
Wow, I'm choking.

206
00:10:19,667 --> 00:10:22,542
[in English] Good hand, Mr. Suwat.
Good hand.

207
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:24,125
[in Thai] Thank you, buddy.

208
00:10:24,625 --> 00:10:26,333
[Andy in English]
The boss also wants to know

209
00:10:26,417 --> 00:10:28,667
about the case of the recycling factory.

210
00:10:30,917 --> 00:10:34,375
It's almost done. Don't worry.

211
00:10:36,042 --> 00:10:37,958
I'll leave it in your hands, Anan.

212
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:40,167
The boss has high hopes on you.

213
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:47,000
[music rises]

214
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:51,000
CRIMINAL COURT

215
00:10:51,083 --> 00:10:55,208
VERDICT DAY:
THE ORDINATION CEREMONY SHOOTING CASE

216
00:10:55,292 --> 00:10:56,667
- [music fades]
- [chains jangling]

217
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:12,083
[in Thai] If I go back to prison
this time,

218
00:11:12,167 --> 00:11:13,875
it'll be for a long time.

219
00:11:13,958 --> 00:11:15,875
Don't you worry too much, Dad.

220
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:18,625
I already told Tawan's friends

221
00:11:18,708 --> 00:11:20,875
to come drink with you every now and then.

222
00:11:20,958 --> 00:11:23,250
[soft tense music playing]

223
00:11:44,917 --> 00:11:46,625
[music fades]

224
00:11:46,708 --> 00:11:50,583
Plaintiff and defendant
in case number O.55/2568.

225
00:11:50,667 --> 00:11:52,333
Is everyone present?

226
00:11:52,417 --> 00:11:53,792
Yes, Your Honor.

227
00:12:01,292 --> 00:12:04,792
In the matter of criminal case 55/2568,

228
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:08,667
the State, represented by
the Public Prosecutor's Office,

229
00:12:08,750 --> 00:12:11,458
versus the defendant,
Mr. Sataban Saengruangnop.

230
00:12:11,542 --> 00:12:14,000
- [tense music playing]
- The plaintiff has filed charges stating

231
00:12:14,083 --> 00:12:16,208
that the defendant,
Mr. Sataban Saengruangnop…

232
00:12:16,292 --> 00:12:19,292
[muffled] …is guilty of the crime
of premeditated murder.

233
00:12:19,375 --> 00:12:23,417
The defendant used a firearm to shoot
and kill the victim, Mr. Kongkiat.

234
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:26,917
The crime took place during
an ordination ceremony on June 10th.

235
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:28,333
- [music stops]
- [sound unmuffles]

236
00:12:28,417 --> 00:12:29,917
This court dismisses all charges.

237
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,500
- The defendant is found not guilty.
- [tense music resumes]

238
00:12:32,583 --> 00:12:34,417
[judge 2] The defendant is to be released.

239
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,708
This court is now adjourned.

240
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:39,375
[chains jangling]

241
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:43,583
[sobbing]

242
00:12:46,333 --> 00:12:48,750
[Jittri]<i> That's how a lawyer looks</i>
<i>after winning?</i>

243
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:52,708
[Mek]<i> We won, yes. But I just helped</i>
<i>a murderer walk free.</i>

244
00:12:55,542 --> 00:12:58,042
[Jittri]<i> I don't think</i>
<i>his father sees it that way.</i>

245
00:13:07,083 --> 00:13:09,458
[inaudible]

246
00:13:16,792 --> 00:13:19,750
- [birds chirping]
- [music concludes]

247
00:13:28,917 --> 00:13:34,042
MRS. WIMON PIRIYAWICH

248
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:40,083
[Anan] You come every year without fail.

249
00:13:49,958 --> 00:13:51,625
Has it really been 16 years?

250
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:53,417
Time flies, doesn't it?

251
00:13:55,458 --> 00:13:57,042
What brings you here, General Anan?

252
00:13:58,792 --> 00:14:01,375
This temple is famous for its murals,

253
00:14:01,458 --> 00:14:03,500
so I came by to take a look.

254
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:07,583
I was wondering
if you might have a moment, Judge Rit.

255
00:14:13,417 --> 00:14:17,583
They say the demons that came
to torment the Buddha

256
00:14:18,083 --> 00:14:21,250
were the inner desires that plagued him

257
00:14:21,750 --> 00:14:23,500
and kept him from reaching enlightenment.

258
00:14:25,083 --> 00:14:26,250
[chuckles softly]

259
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:29,000
And look how many there were.

260
00:14:29,083 --> 00:14:31,917
Yet he endured and achieved enlightenment.

261
00:14:34,417 --> 00:14:36,125
It's like being a judge, isn't it?

262
00:14:38,583 --> 00:14:41,667
You must always remain impartial.

263
00:14:42,542 --> 00:14:44,000
Fighting off your own demons.

264
00:14:45,167 --> 00:14:47,000
I'm simply doing my duty.

265
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,917
It's not as grand as you make it sound.

266
00:14:56,042 --> 00:14:59,833
But I still have to wonder
if it's really worth it

267
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:06,208
for the Buddha to sacrifice
even his own wife and child,

268
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:09,083
all to become the Enlightened One.

269
00:15:13,708 --> 00:15:15,292
Just like you did

270
00:15:16,542 --> 00:15:18,417
when you sacrificed your wife's life

271
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:21,333
to uphold what you believed was right.

272
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:23,833
I think you're crossing a line.

273
00:15:23,917 --> 00:15:25,000
Khamsukon.

274
00:15:25,083 --> 00:15:27,542
[foreboding music playing]

275
00:15:30,792 --> 00:15:32,542
Does that surname sound familiar?

276
00:15:35,333 --> 00:15:39,250
It's the maiden name of Jittri,
your son's lawyer.

277
00:15:42,542 --> 00:15:46,500
And you really think Jittri
intends to help your son?

278
00:15:50,583 --> 00:15:52,333
But I can help your son.

279
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:54,833
Why would you want to help him?

280
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:58,750
We've both been through enough pain.

281
00:16:00,167 --> 00:16:01,417
But, of course,

282
00:16:02,250 --> 00:16:04,708
I don't believe in doing things for free.

283
00:16:11,167 --> 00:16:13,542
The case of the recycling plant fire,
right?

284
00:16:15,250 --> 00:16:17,792
The plant owner has already confessed.

285
00:16:19,042 --> 00:16:20,708
Just let the whole thing end.

286
00:16:23,042 --> 00:16:26,000
Not only will you get your son back…

287
00:16:28,583 --> 00:16:29,958
I also guarantee

288
00:16:30,042 --> 00:16:33,500
you'll get the Chief Judge position
you so rightly deserve.

289
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,208
What if I refuse?

290
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:39,958
Don't rush your answer.

291
00:16:40,750 --> 00:16:43,583
It's an important decision.
Think carefully.

292
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:44,750
[inhales deeply]

293
00:16:44,833 --> 00:16:47,125
But there's one thing I want to tell you.

294
00:16:48,125 --> 00:16:50,417
The final chapter for stubborn people

295
00:16:50,500 --> 00:16:54,417
sometimes leaves them with nothing.

296
00:17:00,125 --> 00:17:01,417
And do you know

297
00:17:02,583 --> 00:17:04,292
what the worst part is,

298
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:06,958
about losing my son, Techin?

299
00:17:09,083 --> 00:17:11,958
It's that I have to ask myself every day

300
00:17:12,875 --> 00:17:14,625
where I went wrong.

301
00:17:15,792 --> 00:17:18,542
Or if I failed to protect my own son.

302
00:17:21,917 --> 00:17:24,542
You think I don't understand that feeling?

303
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,292
I know you understand.

304
00:17:28,375 --> 00:17:29,542
And that's why

305
00:17:31,167 --> 00:17:35,125
we shouldn't put ourselves
through the same pain all over again.

306
00:17:36,417 --> 00:17:38,458
To learn the same lessons twice.

307
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:40,792
Don't you agree?

308
00:17:40,875 --> 00:17:42,625
[music intensifies]

309
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,375
- [music concludes]
- [traffic honking]

310
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:04,167
[pen clicking]

311
00:18:05,083 --> 00:18:09,417
[prosecutor] Okay? If the other side
asks questions that cross the line,

312
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,875
don't panic.

313
00:18:10,958 --> 00:18:12,667
I'll object on your behalf.

314
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:14,500
And when it's your turn,

315
00:18:14,583 --> 00:18:16,792
my assistant will come out to get you.

316
00:18:19,958 --> 00:18:22,292
[soft tense music playing]

317
00:18:22,375 --> 00:18:23,917
Why is Mr. Sorn still here?

318
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,875
We helped with his son's case.
He should be gone by now.

319
00:18:26,958 --> 00:18:28,667
What are you so worked up about?

320
00:18:33,375 --> 00:18:35,083
Then helping with Mai's case
was pointless--

321
00:18:35,167 --> 00:18:36,875
Today, we need to get
the golf course guard

322
00:18:36,958 --> 00:18:38,417
to admit there was a gun.

323
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:40,208
That's all you need to focus on.

324
00:18:41,083 --> 00:18:42,875
[indistinct chatter]

325
00:18:55,542 --> 00:19:00,500
PLAINTIFF'S WITNESS HEARING:
THE GOLF COURSE CASE

326
00:19:00,583 --> 00:19:02,708
- [music fades]
- [prosecutor] At 8 p.m.,

327
00:19:02,792 --> 00:19:04,458
while you were in the guard booth,

328
00:19:05,208 --> 00:19:08,458
what did you do after you heard shouting?

329
00:19:10,542 --> 00:19:13,625
I thought people were arguing,
so I ran over to see.

330
00:19:14,250 --> 00:19:17,208
That's when I saw Mr. Mek.

331
00:19:17,292 --> 00:19:20,417
He hit Mr. Techin in the head from behind
with a golf club.

332
00:19:21,083 --> 00:19:24,750
He hit him hard.
Mr. Techin fell face-first.

333
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:26,458
But he didn't stop there.

334
00:19:27,500 --> 00:19:29,625
He hit him again,
three or four more times.

335
00:19:29,708 --> 00:19:31,333
Until Mr. Techin stopped moving.

336
00:19:31,417 --> 00:19:33,417
[ominous music playing]

337
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:38,125
And what was his demeanor
after assaulting the deceased?

338
00:19:38,208 --> 00:19:40,500
He looked furious.

339
00:19:40,583 --> 00:19:42,625
And satisfied, too.

340
00:19:43,417 --> 00:19:45,417
Oh, and I saw him smile.

341
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:48,000
Right after Mr. Techin stopped moving.

342
00:19:48,083 --> 00:19:50,000
[prosecutor] And what happened after that?

343
00:19:50,083 --> 00:19:51,542
[guard] I ran over to them.

344
00:19:52,375 --> 00:19:53,958
He turned, saw me, and tried to run.

345
00:19:54,042 --> 00:19:57,792
But I managed to grab him
and immediately called the police.

346
00:20:01,167 --> 00:20:02,875
[prosecutor] No further questions.

347
00:20:03,583 --> 00:20:05,375
The defense may cross-examine.

348
00:20:05,458 --> 00:20:06,875
[music falls]

349
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:12,250
You said you heard the defendant
and the deceased arguing,

350
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:14,625
while you were in the guard booth.
Is that correct?

351
00:20:17,958 --> 00:20:18,958
Yes.

352
00:20:19,542 --> 00:20:21,542
And what were you doing at the time?

353
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:32,042
[music rises]

354
00:20:32,917 --> 00:20:35,083
- I wasn't doing anything.
- [insects chirping]

355
00:20:35,167 --> 00:20:36,667
Just sitting there.

356
00:20:37,417 --> 00:20:40,083
I like things quiet.

357
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:42,417
According to your testimony,

358
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:46,000
the incident occurred at 8 p.m.
on Tuesday, October 14th.

359
00:20:46,083 --> 00:20:48,500
The same night that the Rodtang fight
was on.

360
00:20:48,583 --> 00:20:51,500
Your favorite boxer was fighting,
and you weren't watching?

361
00:20:54,042 --> 00:20:55,292
I wasn't watching.

362
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:58,250
Oh, right. You like things quiet.

363
00:20:59,292 --> 00:21:02,375
Then how did you know the defendant
and the deceased were arguing?

364
00:21:02,458 --> 00:21:06,583
They were shouting so loudly,
anyone could have heard them.

365
00:21:06,667 --> 00:21:08,458
And it had to be the defendant's voice,

366
00:21:08,542 --> 00:21:11,792
because if it were Mr. Techin's voice,
I would've recognized it.

367
00:21:11,875 --> 00:21:12,958
What did he shout?

368
00:21:14,042 --> 00:21:15,500
Am I allowed to say it?

369
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:18,208
I think he yelled,

370
00:21:18,292 --> 00:21:19,667
"Asshole!"

371
00:21:20,375 --> 00:21:21,917
Or maybe "Bastard."

372
00:21:23,708 --> 00:21:24,833
And you heard that clearly?

373
00:21:24,917 --> 00:21:26,292
Every single word.

374
00:21:27,625 --> 00:21:28,500
[smacks lips]

375
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:31,292
From the guardhouse to the crime scene,

376
00:21:31,375 --> 00:21:34,667
there's a lake in between.
You have to walk around it.

377
00:21:35,667 --> 00:21:38,667
The direct distance is about 250 meters.

378
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:39,958
[golf club thwacks]

379
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:43,833
[echoing whoosh]

380
00:21:47,583 --> 00:21:49,958
[Jittri] That's longer
than two football fields.

381
00:21:52,875 --> 00:21:54,667
And you're sure you heard him?

382
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:57,083
That the defendant said,

383
00:21:57,167 --> 00:21:58,250
"Asshole."

384
00:21:58,833 --> 00:22:02,625
It may be far, but I have good hearing.

385
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:05,000
I heard it clearly.

386
00:22:05,625 --> 00:22:08,708
You testified that you saw the defendant
hit the victim with a golf club.

387
00:22:08,792 --> 00:22:10,625
How high did the defendant raise the club?

388
00:22:10,708 --> 00:22:12,375
To his chest, or higher?

389
00:22:12,458 --> 00:22:15,333
Oh, come on. He swung with all his might.

390
00:22:15,417 --> 00:22:17,375
He was trying to kill him.

391
00:22:17,458 --> 00:22:20,042
- How many times did he hit him?
- Three.

392
00:22:20,958 --> 00:22:22,250
Or maybe four times.

393
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:23,917
So was it three times or four?

394
00:22:24,708 --> 00:22:26,583
I was in shock at the time.

395
00:22:26,667 --> 00:22:28,000
Who would've counted?

396
00:22:28,083 --> 00:22:29,833
So he hit him several times.

397
00:22:29,917 --> 00:22:32,833
You saw a man get hit several times
and just stood there and watched?

398
00:22:32,917 --> 00:22:34,708
You didn't shout or try to help?

399
00:22:34,792 --> 00:22:36,375
I'm not an idiot.

400
00:22:36,458 --> 00:22:38,042
I'm a former police officer.

401
00:22:39,083 --> 00:22:41,167
You have to assess the situation first.

402
00:22:42,042 --> 00:22:46,125
I had to think of my own safety first,
in case I got hit by a stray.

403
00:22:46,208 --> 00:22:48,542
A stray? From that far?

404
00:22:48,625 --> 00:22:50,792
The defendant only had a golf club.

405
00:22:50,875 --> 00:22:52,708
Or was this "stray" you mentioned

406
00:22:53,708 --> 00:22:55,083
a stray bullet?

407
00:22:55,875 --> 00:22:57,500
[music turns tense]

408
00:22:59,083 --> 00:23:00,042
[chuckles]

409
00:23:02,500 --> 00:23:04,500
A golf club can be dangerous, you know.

410
00:23:05,458 --> 00:23:07,917
So, I had to assess
the situation carefully.

411
00:23:09,458 --> 00:23:11,000
I have no further questions.

412
00:23:11,958 --> 00:23:13,292
[music fades]

413
00:23:13,375 --> 00:23:15,250
Does the prosecution have a redirect?

414
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:16,833
[lawyer] No, Your Honor.

415
00:23:19,583 --> 00:23:21,042
[judge] Next witness, prosecution.

416
00:23:22,333 --> 00:23:25,000
[lawyer] The prosecution calls
Mr. Sorn Saengruangnop

417
00:23:25,083 --> 00:23:26,458
of the Royal Forest Department.

418
00:23:26,542 --> 00:23:28,708
He was the second person to find the body.

419
00:23:33,833 --> 00:23:37,333
Mr. Sorn Saengruangnop,
please come to the witness stand.

420
00:23:37,917 --> 00:23:41,125
[crowd murmuring]

421
00:23:47,042 --> 00:23:50,417
Mr. Sorn Saengruangnop,
please report to the witness stand.

422
00:23:52,417 --> 00:23:53,500
[door opens]

423
00:24:00,125 --> 00:24:02,708
[quietly] Sir,
the witness has disappeared.

424
00:24:02,792 --> 00:24:05,625
What do you mean? Call him, then.

425
00:24:05,708 --> 00:24:08,167
[assistant] I've called
both his numbers, sir. Both are off.

426
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:10,625
- [suspenseful music playing]
- Uh, Your Honor.

427
00:24:10,708 --> 00:24:12,500
The witness had an urgent matter
to attend to.

428
00:24:12,583 --> 00:24:14,833
- I'd like to call another witness--
- Objection.

429
00:24:14,917 --> 00:24:16,792
This is a key witness.

430
00:24:16,875 --> 00:24:19,875
If the prosecution is not prepared,
I request a postponement.

431
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:22,708
Wait a minute. He's my witness.

432
00:24:23,208 --> 00:24:25,792
Whether I call him or not
is none of your business.

433
00:24:25,875 --> 00:24:29,167
Let's let the court decide that, shall we?

434
00:24:29,250 --> 00:24:31,833
Why does the defense
wish to question this witness?

435
00:24:31,917 --> 00:24:33,667
He was the second person to find the body.

436
00:24:33,750 --> 00:24:35,167
That makes him very important.

437
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:39,042
I believe he may have credible information
that is beneficial to the defendant.

438
00:24:39,125 --> 00:24:43,542
In that case,
the prosecution withdraws this witness

439
00:24:43,625 --> 00:24:45,500
and will proceed to the next.

440
00:24:45,583 --> 00:24:49,208
But the defense still wishes
to cross-examine this witness.

441
00:24:49,292 --> 00:24:51,458
I ask the court to issue a summons.

442
00:25:01,833 --> 00:25:05,583
PUBLIC GALLERY

443
00:25:05,667 --> 00:25:07,500
[music concludes]

444
00:25:07,583 --> 00:25:11,500
The court has considered the matter
and will postpone the hearing.

445
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:15,208
In the meantime, the prosecution
will locate the witness

446
00:25:15,875 --> 00:25:19,500
and submit a written explanation
as to why he was absent today.

447
00:25:21,208 --> 00:25:24,833
Counselor, do not let this happen again.

448
00:25:26,042 --> 00:25:28,250
This court is adjourned for the day.

449
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:30,708
- [crowd chattering]
- [soft tense music playing]

450
00:25:39,792 --> 00:25:41,167
[Jittri] Hello, Mr. Anan.

451
00:25:41,667 --> 00:25:45,500
You're much more distinguished
in person than on TV.

452
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:50,458
And you, Attorney Jittri, are prettier
than you appear on the news.

453
00:25:52,667 --> 00:25:54,625
Why do you look so familiar to me?

454
00:25:55,125 --> 00:25:58,125
It's as if we've met somewhere before.

455
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:00,542
I'm not sure.

456
00:26:01,125 --> 00:26:03,333
But if I had met someone like you,

457
00:26:03,417 --> 00:26:05,083
I'd never forget.

458
00:26:05,167 --> 00:26:06,708
[music rises]

459
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,958
If there's anything you need,
please don't hesitate to call.

460
00:26:13,542 --> 00:26:14,542
Ah.

461
00:26:14,625 --> 00:26:15,833
Now I remember.

462
00:26:16,708 --> 00:26:19,542
You look just like your mother.

463
00:26:24,583 --> 00:26:26,083
Is your mother doing well?

464
00:26:28,000 --> 00:26:29,542
She's doing very well.

465
00:26:30,708 --> 00:26:32,708
In fact, she was just asking about you.

466
00:26:32,792 --> 00:26:36,708
She was wondering when you might come by
to taste some of her desserts.

467
00:26:41,625 --> 00:26:42,917
Excuse me.

468
00:26:44,042 --> 00:26:46,667
[music intensifies]

469
00:26:53,917 --> 00:26:56,042
[music fades]

470
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,500
[Kung] I'll bring my wife there.

471
00:26:58,583 --> 00:27:01,208
You eat so much candy,
your teeth will all fall out.

472
00:27:01,292 --> 00:27:02,958
[Meuk] Mek's here.
Is the charcoal lit yet?

473
00:27:03,042 --> 00:27:05,125
- [Kung] Hurry, add more charcoal!
- [Nemo] Let's do it.

474
00:27:05,208 --> 00:27:08,542
[Kung] Hurry up and put it in.
Nitrogen oxide or whatever this is.

475
00:27:09,417 --> 00:27:10,500
Just blast it.

476
00:27:12,625 --> 00:27:14,292
- Vegetables.
- Oh.

477
00:27:14,375 --> 00:27:17,500
[Kung chattering]

478
00:27:17,583 --> 00:27:18,750
Where's Jittri?

479
00:27:18,833 --> 00:27:21,250
She came back
and went straight to her room.

480
00:27:22,167 --> 00:27:23,167
Ah.

481
00:27:25,125 --> 00:27:27,583
Here, want to help?

482
00:27:28,542 --> 00:27:29,583
Sure.

483
00:27:30,833 --> 00:27:32,417
So the hearing was postponed?

484
00:27:34,292 --> 00:27:35,417
Yes.

485
00:27:35,500 --> 00:27:36,542
[Noi] Hmm.

486
00:27:37,083 --> 00:27:40,500
You know, it's really hard to get
a postponement in a case like this.

487
00:27:41,458 --> 00:27:43,042
But Jittri is brilliant.

488
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:46,458
This buys us another three or four months.

489
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:50,333
Did you use to work at the courthouse?

490
00:27:52,958 --> 00:27:54,708
I used to be a court clerk.

491
00:27:56,042 --> 00:27:58,417
I did it for almost 30 years.

492
00:28:00,292 --> 00:28:01,792
I've seen it all.

493
00:28:03,125 --> 00:28:05,333
Framing scapegoats, broken cameras…

494
00:28:06,125 --> 00:28:07,125
[chuckles softly]

495
00:28:07,208 --> 00:28:09,458
I just kept my head down and typed.

496
00:28:11,083 --> 00:28:13,167
There was one case near the border.

497
00:28:13,958 --> 00:28:15,833
The father went missing.

498
00:28:17,167 --> 00:28:19,583
The mother and her kid
tried to seek justice.

499
00:28:19,667 --> 00:28:21,583
They went to the police.

500
00:28:22,708 --> 00:28:25,125
But none of the local police

501
00:28:25,208 --> 00:28:28,292
would file a case for them.

502
00:28:30,333 --> 00:28:31,625
And you know what?

503
00:28:32,833 --> 00:28:35,000
Who were the mother
and the kid up against?

504
00:28:37,792 --> 00:28:39,250
The police.

505
00:28:46,167 --> 00:28:49,500
Jittri's methods
aren't exactly by the book.

506
00:28:50,917 --> 00:28:53,750
But when the system is this crooked,

507
00:28:53,833 --> 00:28:57,542
you shouldn't feel guilty
for exploiting it a little.

508
00:29:03,375 --> 00:29:04,458
[chuckles softly]

509
00:29:05,667 --> 00:29:08,458
I didn't make you feel
any less guilty, did I?

510
00:29:09,750 --> 00:29:11,250
[laughs]

511
00:29:13,333 --> 00:29:16,083
- [group cheers]
- Hey, it's lit!

512
00:29:16,167 --> 00:29:18,833
- Damn, it took you-- Whoa.
- [Nemo] Here, smell it.

513
00:29:18,917 --> 00:29:21,875
Want to get sick eating raw pork?
Are you high?

514
00:29:21,958 --> 00:29:24,750
What? You want Wi-Fi?
Go pay for your own internet.

515
00:29:24,833 --> 00:29:27,125
- Nice. Share it then.
- I'm starving.

516
00:29:27,208 --> 00:29:28,583
Auntie, Wi-Fi.

517
00:29:28,667 --> 00:29:30,625
How did you end up with these guys?

518
00:29:31,417 --> 00:29:34,125
[Noi] It was Jittri.
She helped out Kung and Nemo.

519
00:29:34,708 --> 00:29:37,208
They're all just kids from around here.

520
00:29:37,292 --> 00:29:39,667
They were tricked into
working for a call center scam.

521
00:29:39,750 --> 00:29:42,083
Then one day,
when the police raided the place,

522
00:29:42,167 --> 00:29:44,792
the gang leader framed Kung
to take the fall.

523
00:29:44,875 --> 00:29:47,208
So Jittri went and became his lawyer.

524
00:29:47,708 --> 00:29:50,542
As for Meuk, he's Kung's younger brother.

525
00:29:50,625 --> 00:29:52,750
- [Mek] Hmm?
- [Noi] They don't look alike, do they?

526
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:53,708
[laughs]

527
00:29:55,875 --> 00:29:57,625
It may seem like
they're just messing around,

528
00:29:57,708 --> 00:29:59,708
but when it's time to get serious,

529
00:29:59,792 --> 00:30:02,250
they're a huge help to Jittri.

530
00:30:02,333 --> 00:30:04,292
Mom, where's the pot?

531
00:30:04,375 --> 00:30:07,792
[Noi] What? Why didn't you bring it up?

532
00:30:07,875 --> 00:30:10,542
- [indistinct chatter]
- Why are you asking me?

533
00:30:10,625 --> 00:30:13,375
I'll go get it. I'm done with this anyway.

534
00:30:13,458 --> 00:30:15,000
Ah. Okay.

535
00:30:15,083 --> 00:30:16,750
Whoa, we have a volunteer.

536
00:30:16,833 --> 00:30:18,833
Wow, thanks, bro.

537
00:30:18,917 --> 00:30:21,958
Damn, that's a nice shirt.
I'd button that thing to the top.

538
00:30:22,042 --> 00:30:24,083
Dude, they don't make it in your size.

539
00:30:24,167 --> 00:30:25,208
[Noi chuckles]

540
00:30:26,208 --> 00:30:27,708
Come and get this.

541
00:30:27,792 --> 00:30:30,792
Just a minute.
Let's wait for the pot first.

542
00:30:31,292 --> 00:30:32,667
[Noi] Oh!

543
00:30:32,750 --> 00:30:35,292
We wait. Pot arrives, boom.
Veggies in, bam.

544
00:30:35,375 --> 00:30:37,333
Then the meat. Ready to eat.

545
00:30:37,417 --> 00:30:38,750
[group exclaims]

546
00:30:51,250 --> 00:30:52,125
Hold on.

547
00:30:53,792 --> 00:30:54,708
[door opens]

548
00:30:55,667 --> 00:30:58,167
In our next case,
the defendant is a doctor.

549
00:30:58,250 --> 00:31:00,250
He's being sued by a patient
for sexual assault.

550
00:31:00,333 --> 00:31:02,625
DR. KORN'S CASE

551
00:31:02,708 --> 00:31:05,333
We have to help the doctor
because of your case.

552
00:31:05,417 --> 00:31:08,917
We need him to fabricate evidence
that you couldn't have killed Techin.

553
00:31:09,958 --> 00:31:11,375
Are they ready upstairs?

554
00:31:12,958 --> 00:31:15,000
You were acting strange in court today.

555
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:19,500
[Jittri] How so?

556
00:31:20,500 --> 00:31:22,458
You already know Anan, don't you?

557
00:31:23,583 --> 00:31:25,458
He did something to you in the past,
didn't he?

558
00:31:25,542 --> 00:31:27,875
[dark pensive music playing]

559
00:31:30,875 --> 00:31:33,333
If you don't tell me
the real reason you took my case,

560
00:31:33,417 --> 00:31:35,083
how can I trust you?

561
00:31:38,667 --> 00:31:40,583
I just want to see Anan suffer.

562
00:31:46,167 --> 00:31:49,792
What's more painful than seeing
the person who killed your kid walk free?

563
00:31:50,375 --> 00:31:51,667
Right?

564
00:31:56,958 --> 00:31:59,667
[door opens, closes]

565
00:32:01,708 --> 00:32:03,167
[music fades]

566
00:32:03,250 --> 00:32:05,708
[indistinct chatter]

567
00:32:09,292 --> 00:32:11,792
[doctor] Your lungs don't
sound good at all.

568
00:32:11,875 --> 00:32:14,042
Why did you let it get this bad?

569
00:32:14,792 --> 00:32:17,750
I live on a boat.
I don't have any medicine.

570
00:32:20,417 --> 00:32:22,833
[doctor] This is the first time
we've met, right?

571
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:28,208
Okay, I'll prescribe you some medicine.

572
00:32:30,917 --> 00:32:31,917
Thank you.

573
00:32:38,500 --> 00:32:41,375
[tense music playing]

574
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:45,667
[running footsteps]

575
00:32:46,250 --> 00:32:48,250
[man in Burmese]
The police are coming to arrest him!

576
00:32:49,042 --> 00:32:50,125
The police are here!

577
00:32:50,833 --> 00:32:51,833
Follow me!

578
00:32:52,458 --> 00:32:54,833
[Seya in Thai] Why are you arresting me?

579
00:32:54,917 --> 00:32:56,333
Let go!

580
00:32:56,417 --> 00:32:58,125
[in Burmese] Take this
and record everything.

581
00:32:58,208 --> 00:33:00,292
- [in Thai] Let go!
- Don't resist.

582
00:33:00,375 --> 00:33:02,292
[Pang] Where are you taking this boy?

583
00:33:02,375 --> 00:33:03,833
[music fades]

584
00:33:05,958 --> 00:33:07,042
Please calm down, ma'am.

585
00:33:07,125 --> 00:33:10,333
This boy's older sister
assaulted her employer and fled.

586
00:33:10,417 --> 00:33:12,750
We believe he helped her escape.

587
00:33:12,833 --> 00:33:14,125
What sister?

588
00:33:14,625 --> 00:33:16,375
[in Burmese] Seya, you have a sister?

589
00:33:19,708 --> 00:33:22,583
[in Thai] Is Miss Nay Oo,
age 20, your sister?

590
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,500
[in Burmese] Is that true?

591
00:33:29,625 --> 00:33:32,042
[foreboding music playing]

592
00:33:36,083 --> 00:33:39,292
[in Thai] If his sister did
something wrong, it's not his fault.

593
00:33:39,375 --> 00:33:42,458
And if you're taking him in
for questioning as a witness,

594
00:33:42,542 --> 00:33:44,708
you need a warrant. Do you have one?

595
00:33:46,208 --> 00:33:48,792
We just want to ask him
a few informal questions.

596
00:33:48,875 --> 00:33:50,375
Then ask him here.

597
00:33:50,458 --> 00:33:51,917
I'm staying to listen.

598
00:33:55,125 --> 00:33:58,208
So, no questions and no warrant.

599
00:33:58,292 --> 00:34:00,042
But you're still going to take him?

600
00:34:03,375 --> 00:34:05,583
I have a lot of contacts in the media.

601
00:34:05,667 --> 00:34:07,542
Police brutality stories…

602
00:34:08,417 --> 00:34:09,625
The media loves that.

603
00:34:11,708 --> 00:34:13,792
[foreboding music continues]

604
00:34:18,042 --> 00:34:19,958
[music rises]

605
00:34:21,083 --> 00:34:22,125
Let him go.

606
00:34:22,208 --> 00:34:23,708
[music falls]

607
00:34:26,708 --> 00:34:29,208
[indistinct chatter]

608
00:34:33,333 --> 00:34:34,917
[in Burmese] Your sister?

609
00:34:39,292 --> 00:34:40,292
Yes.

610
00:34:42,583 --> 00:34:44,625
[music fades]

611
00:34:47,167 --> 00:34:49,583
[nurse in Thai] Ms. Malisa,
you can go in now.

612
00:34:52,333 --> 00:34:53,833
Right this way.

613
00:34:57,417 --> 00:34:58,958
- [Meuk screaming]
- [Nemo] Help, please!

614
00:34:59,042 --> 00:35:01,042
My uncle's shoulder is dislocated!

615
00:35:01,125 --> 00:35:03,375
- Uncle!
- [intriguing music playing]

616
00:35:03,458 --> 00:35:05,000
- [screaming]
- Please help!

617
00:35:05,083 --> 00:35:06,458
His shoulder's dislocated.

618
00:35:06,542 --> 00:35:08,750
- [yelps]
- He's really hurt.

619
00:35:08,833 --> 00:35:10,542
[nurse] Let's put some ice on it.

620
00:35:10,625 --> 00:35:12,042
I'll get the doctor.

621
00:35:12,125 --> 00:35:14,250
- [thud]
- [Mek] Uh…

622
00:35:14,333 --> 00:35:17,333
Excuse me, do you have a mop?
I'll clean it up.

623
00:35:17,417 --> 00:35:18,958
It's alright. I'll go get one.

624
00:35:19,042 --> 00:35:21,583
- [Meuk screaming]
- [Nemo speaking indistinctly]

625
00:35:21,667 --> 00:35:23,333
- [music stops]
- [echoing ding]

626
00:35:23,417 --> 00:35:25,042
- [Meuk screams]
- [intriguing music resumes]

627
00:35:25,125 --> 00:35:27,208
[Nemo speaking indistinctly]

628
00:35:27,292 --> 00:35:29,750
- [Nemo] Excuse me!
- Please wait a moment.

629
00:35:29,833 --> 00:35:32,208
DR. KORN SOPHONCHITRAK

630
00:35:32,292 --> 00:35:33,542
[music concludes]

631
00:35:33,625 --> 00:35:35,125
[Korn] Does it hurt here?

632
00:35:36,125 --> 00:35:39,375
Mm. Yes, it's kind of achy.

633
00:35:40,583 --> 00:35:43,958
Sometimes, when it flares up,
I can barely lift my arm.

634
00:35:44,042 --> 00:35:46,667
[Korn] Mm-hmm. And how about this?

635
00:35:48,375 --> 00:35:49,833
- Does it hurt?
- [groans]

636
00:35:51,167 --> 00:35:53,250
- It feels tense, Doctor.
- [Korn] Hmm.

637
00:35:54,667 --> 00:35:56,792
But when you massage it like this, it…

638
00:35:57,417 --> 00:35:59,917
- it feels good.
- [intriguing music playing]

639
00:36:00,000 --> 00:36:01,292
[Korn] Mm…

640
00:36:02,833 --> 00:36:06,083
In that case, I'll prescribe
some muscle relaxants for you.

641
00:36:06,167 --> 00:36:07,250
[Jittri moans softly]

642
00:36:07,792 --> 00:36:10,500
But sometimes the pain
spreads through my whole body.

643
00:36:11,333 --> 00:36:13,792
I'd like you to do
a more thorough examination

644
00:36:13,875 --> 00:36:15,500
since I'm already here.

645
00:36:15,583 --> 00:36:17,500
[music fades]

646
00:36:19,208 --> 00:36:20,625
A thorough examination?

647
00:36:21,250 --> 00:36:23,667
- [lock clicks]
- [dreamy intriguing music playing]

648
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:38,208
[Jittri moans]

649
00:36:41,042 --> 00:36:42,250
[moans softly]

650
00:36:43,042 --> 00:36:44,542
That tickles.

651
00:36:45,875 --> 00:36:46,875
Do you like it?

652
00:36:49,250 --> 00:36:52,708
Why are you unzipping my dress?
I thought you said I wouldn't have to.

653
00:36:52,792 --> 00:36:54,125
I changed my mind.

654
00:36:54,792 --> 00:36:56,875
It's better if you take it off.

655
00:36:56,958 --> 00:36:58,250
So I can examine more easily.

656
00:36:58,333 --> 00:37:01,333
Isn't a nurse supposed
to be present for this?

657
00:37:01,417 --> 00:37:04,542
That's not necessary.
It's just a quick exam.

658
00:37:04,625 --> 00:37:06,125
And do others take theirs off?

659
00:37:06,875 --> 00:37:08,292
[Korn] It depends on the person.

660
00:37:08,375 --> 00:37:11,083
But everyone who takes it off is cured.

661
00:37:11,167 --> 00:37:12,667
Everyone…

662
00:37:14,250 --> 00:37:16,333
- [music concludes]
- Does that include Pui?

663
00:37:21,875 --> 00:37:25,042
What's so confusing?
Or have you already forgotten?

664
00:37:25,125 --> 00:37:26,000
[clicks tongue]

665
00:37:26,083 --> 00:37:28,042
But how could you forget
the person who sued you

666
00:37:28,125 --> 00:37:30,500
for sexual assault and rape?

667
00:37:31,417 --> 00:37:33,500
[hesitates] Who are you?

668
00:37:33,583 --> 00:37:35,208
What… What do you want?

669
00:37:36,625 --> 00:37:37,917
I'm a lawyer.

670
00:37:38,458 --> 00:37:41,083
- [scoffs] Oh…
- [tense music playing]

671
00:37:41,167 --> 00:37:44,208
Go tell them my offer is final.

672
00:37:44,875 --> 00:37:47,792
If they want more than that,
we can settle it in court.

673
00:37:48,583 --> 00:37:50,333
I'm afraid I can't do that.

674
00:37:50,417 --> 00:37:52,083
Because I'm not Pui's lawyer.

675
00:37:53,375 --> 00:37:55,042
Do you have a lawyer yet?

676
00:37:55,125 --> 00:37:56,625
I'd like to offer my services.

677
00:37:57,917 --> 00:38:00,083
I can guarantee you'll win Pui's case

678
00:38:00,750 --> 00:38:03,375
in return for your help
on another case I'm handling.

679
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:07,167
My client is accused of hitting someone
with a golf club.

680
00:38:07,250 --> 00:38:10,125
All you have to do is testify
that he's too weak to lift the club.

681
00:38:10,208 --> 00:38:13,292
Well… How can I do something like that?

682
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:15,958
That's against medical ethics.

683
00:38:16,042 --> 00:38:17,875
You still don't get it, Doctor?

684
00:38:17,958 --> 00:38:19,917
You're in no position to negotiate.

685
00:38:20,667 --> 00:38:22,750
My associate recorded
our whole conversation.

686
00:38:22,833 --> 00:38:24,000
KUNG

687
00:38:24,833 --> 00:38:26,583
It can be kept a secret

688
00:38:26,667 --> 00:38:29,000
or it can be sent to the opposing counsel.

689
00:38:29,833 --> 00:38:31,417
The choice is yours, Doctor.

690
00:38:37,625 --> 00:38:40,083
[music intensifies]

691
00:38:47,292 --> 00:38:48,750
[Mek] How'd you get him to agree?

692
00:38:48,833 --> 00:38:50,042
[music concludes]

693
00:38:50,125 --> 00:38:51,875
Blackmail, obviously.

694
00:38:53,208 --> 00:38:55,958
But audio recordings aren't admissible.
They won't hold up.

695
00:38:56,042 --> 00:38:57,208
I know.

696
00:38:57,292 --> 00:38:58,458
But he doesn't.

697
00:38:59,667 --> 00:39:01,000
[engine starts]

698
00:39:02,375 --> 00:39:06,708
[cell phone ringing]

699
00:39:06,792 --> 00:39:08,167
[seatbelts clicking]

700
00:39:09,208 --> 00:39:11,667
- What's up, Ang?
- [Ang] <i>Where are you, Mek?</i>

701
00:39:11,750 --> 00:39:13,125
<i>Can you come see me right now?</i>

702
00:39:13,208 --> 00:39:15,708
[foreboding music playing]

703
00:39:15,792 --> 00:39:18,542
- This way, quick! Car's coming! Hurry!
- [kids laughing, yelling]

704
00:39:18,625 --> 00:39:19,792
Hurry up!

705
00:39:24,875 --> 00:39:27,250
[foreboding music continues]

706
00:39:34,875 --> 00:39:37,875
This is Pang.
She's helping us find Nay Oo.

707
00:39:39,208 --> 00:39:40,458
Pang, this is Mek.

708
00:39:42,333 --> 00:39:44,833
Seya was forced to work as a laborer
on a fishing boat.

709
00:39:44,917 --> 00:39:46,708
He doesn't trust people easily.

710
00:39:46,792 --> 00:39:49,708
But I told him you'd be here
to talk to him today.

711
00:39:50,292 --> 00:39:51,542
There's Seya.

712
00:39:56,708 --> 00:39:57,792
[music concludes]

713
00:39:57,875 --> 00:39:59,583
[Ang] We really want to help Nay Oo.

714
00:40:00,750 --> 00:40:02,333
Nay Oo is in danger.

715
00:40:03,458 --> 00:40:05,125
Do you know where she is?

716
00:40:07,750 --> 00:40:10,167
I haven't spoken to my sister
in a long time.

717
00:40:11,417 --> 00:40:13,125
They separated us.

718
00:40:14,042 --> 00:40:16,292
I was sent to work on a fishing boat.

719
00:40:17,417 --> 00:40:20,250
And my sisters were sent
to work in Bangkok.

720
00:40:23,083 --> 00:40:24,792
How long is "a long time"?

721
00:40:25,292 --> 00:40:26,958
A few months? A year?

722
00:40:27,708 --> 00:40:30,292
Probably almost three years.

723
00:40:31,167 --> 00:40:34,625
On a boat, you lose track of time.

724
00:40:34,708 --> 00:40:37,500
Then why are the police
still looking for Nay Oo here?

725
00:40:40,583 --> 00:40:41,917
I don't know.

726
00:40:45,042 --> 00:40:46,958
You don't know, or you won't tell?

727
00:40:47,708 --> 00:40:50,000
[soft tense music playing]

728
00:40:51,417 --> 00:40:53,000
I really don't know.

729
00:41:04,167 --> 00:41:05,292
Seya.

730
00:41:06,083 --> 00:41:08,667
I get that you want to protect Nay Oo.

731
00:41:09,625 --> 00:41:11,875
But what's happening now is very serious.

732
00:41:11,958 --> 00:41:13,375
You can't handle this alone.

733
00:41:14,875 --> 00:41:16,292
Let us help you, Seya.

734
00:41:18,750 --> 00:41:20,500
Please, I'm asking you.

735
00:41:22,125 --> 00:41:24,875
Your sister's in danger.
Please let me help.

736
00:41:27,042 --> 00:41:29,458
Why would you want to help my sister?

737
00:41:31,250 --> 00:41:33,208
What your sister did was very serious.

738
00:41:33,292 --> 00:41:35,083
My sister didn't kill anyone.

739
00:41:35,167 --> 00:41:37,167
[music rises]

740
00:41:38,625 --> 00:41:41,417
The police just said she assaulted
her employer, didn't they?

741
00:41:41,500 --> 00:41:43,000
Where did you hear about a murder?

742
00:41:44,167 --> 00:41:46,625
Where'd you hear that?
You know, don't you?

743
00:41:47,250 --> 00:41:50,042
- Talk, or we'll go to the police!
- [Pang] Stop! Hey! That's enough!

744
00:41:50,125 --> 00:41:52,000
- [Mek] But he's lying!
- What is wrong with you?

745
00:41:52,083 --> 00:41:54,042
[Mek] Let's all go
to the police right now!

746
00:41:54,125 --> 00:41:55,125
What is it, Ang?

747
00:41:55,208 --> 00:41:57,083
- The kid is lying!
- [Ang] Why are you doing this?

748
00:41:57,167 --> 00:41:59,375
- I'll call the cops!
- He's scared. Are you crazy?

749
00:41:59,458 --> 00:42:00,625
[Mek] He's lying.

750
00:42:00,708 --> 00:42:03,292
You barely talked to him.
How do you know that?

751
00:42:03,375 --> 00:42:07,250
Everything he's said is a lie, Ang.
He said he was separated from his sister.

752
00:42:07,333 --> 00:42:09,875
Separated at the border?
How'd he know she was in Bangkok?

753
00:42:09,958 --> 00:42:11,750
And then he said
his sister didn't kill anyone.

754
00:42:11,833 --> 00:42:13,375
I'm the one who told Pang.

755
00:42:13,458 --> 00:42:14,458
[music fades]

756
00:42:14,542 --> 00:42:17,375
I told Pang she was on the run
for a murder charge.

757
00:42:17,917 --> 00:42:19,375
Mek, why are you being like this?

758
00:42:19,458 --> 00:42:20,792
Get a grip.

759
00:42:22,375 --> 00:42:24,417
We're going to find her no matter what.

760
00:42:24,500 --> 00:42:26,083
Just not like this.

761
00:42:26,958 --> 00:42:28,125
Understand?

762
00:42:34,250 --> 00:42:35,583
I'm sorry, then.

763
00:42:36,458 --> 00:42:38,375
[soft tense music playing]

764
00:42:40,292 --> 00:42:41,542
[car door opens]

765
00:42:41,625 --> 00:42:43,000
[engine starts]

766
00:42:49,000 --> 00:42:50,292
[in Burmese] It's alright now.

767
00:42:53,917 --> 00:42:57,625
[music rises]

768
00:42:59,667 --> 00:43:02,208
[faint chatter]

769
00:43:15,458 --> 00:43:18,417
[woman] Wow, that's a lot.
Where are you taking all this?

770
00:43:18,500 --> 00:43:20,708
I have to go. Thank you.

771
00:43:20,792 --> 00:43:21,958
[woman] Okay.

772
00:43:24,875 --> 00:43:27,875
- [indistinct chatter]
- [tense music continues]

773
00:43:44,250 --> 00:43:48,000
[dogs barking in the distance]

774
00:43:50,875 --> 00:43:51,917
[keys jangle]

775
00:43:54,708 --> 00:43:56,583
[keys jangling]

776
00:44:00,250 --> 00:44:02,083
[music concludes]

777
00:44:02,167 --> 00:44:03,167
[door closes]

778
00:44:03,917 --> 00:44:06,125
[light buzzing faintly]

779
00:44:28,500 --> 00:44:30,083
Have you been waiting long?

780
00:44:34,083 --> 00:44:36,917
It'll be hard for us to move around now.

781
00:44:38,042 --> 00:44:41,792
People are investigating you, Nay Oo.

782
00:44:43,875 --> 00:44:46,708
[dark intriguing music playing]

783
00:44:55,250 --> 00:44:58,125
[music continues, intensifies]

784
00:46:03,708 --> 00:46:07,208
[dark tense music playing]

785
00:47:13,792 --> 00:47:15,208
[music concludes]
